OSI model - open system interconnection model is a critical building block for your understanding of networking. It helps you troubleshoot networks, if the cable isn&rsquo;t plugged (Physical - layer 1).  
Layers It consist of layers shown in the figure beneath this text, and the layers are read bottom up. Application, presentation and session layer is the primary focus of developers / SysAdmin / ServerAdmin.
   Layers Number      Application 7 All   Presentation 6 People   Session 5 Sleeping   Transport 4 Through   Network 3 Networking   Datalink 2 Don&rsquo;t   Physical 1 Pass     Easy way to memorize the layers is to remember the sentence &ldquo;All people sleeping through networking don&rsquo;t pass&rdquo;
